f long distance transmission. Our study has elucidated the possible evolutionary origins of \u03b2CoV among African bats; we therefore advocate for broader studies of whole genome sequences of BtCoV to further understand the drivers for their emergence and zoonotic spillovers into human population.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Motayo, Babatunde O.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Oluwasemowo, Olukunle Oluwapamilerin", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Akinduti, Paul A.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/27ff57595724f8a8d1640fb3a9ce06ae", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/f2d4e7ab8e99842f96f4597219e899d9e2cca43ea9c69327eb5e92350513073c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/PHXRU6KK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/PHXRU6KK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/dea1a2c8807f07edea72da12fd865506!/b172569-175034", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"pages": "e10434", "title": "PeerJ", "volume": "8"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/27ff57595724f8a8d1640fb3a9ce06ae"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:PHXRU6KK"}, {"identifier": "10.7717/peerj.10434"}], "communities": [{"id": "biosyslit"},